		"description": {
			"value": "<p><em>Wondrous Item - Legendary</em></p><p><em>This 2-foot-diameter black sphere is a hole in the multiverse, hovering in space and stabilized by a magical field surrounding it.</em></p><p>The sphere obliterates all matter it passes through and all matter that passes through it. Artifacts are the exception. Unless an Artifact is susceptible to damage from a <em>Sphere of Annihilation</em>, it passes through the sphere unscathed. Anything else that touches the sphere but isn't wholly engulfed and obliterated by it takes [[/damage 8d10 Force]] damage.</p><p><strong>Controlling the Sphere</strong></p><p><strong>Action </strong>- 60 ft.</p><p><em>Any creature within 60 ft. of the sphere can take this action.</em></p><p><strong>[[/skill arc 25]](Arcana Check (DC 25)</strong></p><ul><li><p><strong>Success: </strong>You control the sphere until the start of your next turn, and if it was under another creature's control, that creature loses control of the sphere.</p></li><li><p><strong>Failure: </strong>The sphere moves 10 feet toward you in a straight line.</p></li></ul><p><strong>Bonus Action</strong></p><p><em>Trigger: While in control of the sphere</em></p><ul><li><p>Move the sphere in one direction of your choice, up to a number of feet equal to 5 times your Intelligence modifier (minimum 5 feet). Any creature whose space the sphere enters must succeed on a [[/save DEX 19]]{Dexterity Save (DC 19)} or be touched by it, taking [[/damage 8d10 Force]] damage. A creature reduced to 0 Hit Points by this damage is obliterated, leaving its possessions behind but no other physical remains.</p></li><li><p>If the sphere comes into contact with a planar portal (such as that created by the <em>@UUID[Compendium.elkan5e.elkan5e-spells.Item.sJ4UNpnxQJttNXu9]{Gate}</em> spell) or an extradimensional space (such as that within a @UUID[Compendium.elkan5e.elkan5e-magic-items.Item.dmgPortableHole0]{Portable Hole}), the GM determines randomly what happens using the following table.</p></li></ul><p>@Embed[Compendium.dnd5e.tables24.RollTable.dmgSphereOfAnnih]</p>",
